This paper discusses a machine learning approach to decision-making in organizations, which involves using historical data to learn a surrogate model and evolve a decision strategy that optimizes outcomes. The paper also extends this approach to reinforcement learning tasks. Given this content, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), cs.RO (Robotics), cs.SY (Systems and Control), and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
